er());\\n        } catch (SecurityException ex) {\\n        }\\n        \\n        try {\\n            loaders.add(Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader());\\n        } catch (SecurityException ex) {\\n        }\\n        \\n        loaders.add(Init.class.getClassLoader());\\n        \\n        // Remove all the nulls except one - in the case where this is loaded \\n        // from the bootstrap classloader\\n        int nullCount = 0;\\n        for (Iterator<ClassLoader> it = loaders.iterator(); it.hasNext(); ) {\\n            if (it.next() == null && ++nullCount > 1) {\\n                it.remove();\\n            }\\n        }\\n        \\n        return Collections.unmodifiableList(loaders);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static UnsatisfiedLinkError newLoadError(Throwable cause) {\\n        UnsatisfiedLinkError error = new UnsatisfiedLinkError(cause.getLocalizedMessage());\\n        error.initCause(cause);\\n\\n        return error;\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777968518252}}\nforge/logs/com.github.jnr:jffi:1.3.9/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T08-11-10-639054Z.log:452:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering Java test file**\\n\\nI need to add a dedicated Java test file for the active class. It should be a top-level public class, and having it in the current package, com_github_jnr.jffi, is fine. I also need to inspect the source of the Init class to ensure everything aligns properly. This step is important for keeping my code organized and functionally sound. I want to make sure I’m thorough with implementing tests!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_04f40d42bd06a5d10169f9a583b71c8195b26919306f782caf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-aWFxGwkdFHWZ2hX_FsRZpLt2TlHuhboFIPHuDZv1IdJWcBeashUNb_M1Vlg4fw5KV_QoIPlR3KW5WRiGdllm9ZI-BXv2mrUsI_-eGnGOUfQA0YKThznnZMgJisaXyoEvWiN4i8_u2